.TH TIDYMAC 1 "March 2026" "TidyMac v1.0.0" "TidyMac Manual"
.SH NAME
tidymac \- A developer-aware, privacy-first Mac cleanup utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tidymac
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tidymac
is a powerful cleanup utility designed for macOS developers. It identifies and removes unnecessary files like caches, logs, and temporary developer assets (Xcode derived data, Docker images, etc.).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBscan\fR
Scan the system for reclaimable space.
.TP
\fBclean\fR
Remove identified junk files.
.TP
\fBdisk-usage\fR
Show current disk usage breakdown.
.TP
\fBapps\fR
Manage installed applications and leftovers.
.TP
\fBprivacy\fR
Perform a privacy audit (cookies, history).
.TP
\fBdocker\fR
Manage Docker images and containers.
.TP
\fBundo\fR
Restore files from the staging area.
.TP
\fBdiagnostics\fR
Collect logs and system info for support.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-p, \-\-profile <PROFILE>\fR
Select a scan profile (quick, developer, deep).
.TP
\fB\-m, \-\-mode <MODE>\fR
Set cleaning mode (dry-run, soft, hard).
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help information.
.TP
\fB\-V, \-\-version\fR
Print version information.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.tidymac/config.toml\fR
User configuration file.
.TP
\fI~/Library/Logs/TidyMac/tidymac.log\fR
System logs.
.SH AUTHOR
Jeeva Krishnasamy
